    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.113/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-22T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 22, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. At request of Brazilian Government, through Brazilian Ambassador here,<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d459fn9">Note No. 73, October 22; Department of State, <hi
                            rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, October 25, 1930, p. 265.</note>
                    stating that conditions of domestic violence exist in <pb facs="0523" n="443"
                        xml:id="pg_443"/> certain portions of Brazil, the President today issued a
                    Proclamation prohibiting the export of arms and munitions of war to Brazil
                    except under license of the Secretary of State.<note n="10" xml:id="d459fn10">46
                        Stat. 3036; Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>,
                        October 25, 1930, p. 264.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
